   "source": [
    "# SOS Multiple Language Example\n",
    "Script of Scripts (SOS) enables multiple languages (matlab, python, etc) to be used in a single jupyter notebook. \n",
    "\n",
    "[running SOS](https://vatlab.github.io/sos-docs/running.html#content)\n",
    "\n",
    "## Installation\n",
    "To install for jupyter notebook:\n",
    "```\n",
    "pip3 install sos\n",
    "pip3 install sos-notebook\n",
    "python3 -m sos_notebook.install\n",
    "```\n",
    "To install jupyterLab extension (note that this transient-display-data only supported for jupyterLab 1.0.0 alpha so it may be best to wait for the 1.0.0 releast to install. However SOS still currently works for notebooks in jupyterLab). \n",
    "```\n",
    "jupyter labextension install transient-display-data\n",
    "jupyter labextension install jupyterlab-sos\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "In a SOS notebook, the dropdown menu on the right side of each block is used to set the language kernel."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "python3"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Python in SOS\n",
    "Python3 will be installed by default"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "python3"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "hello world\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"hello world\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "python3"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Octave in SOS\n",
    "Once Octave and SOS are installed, install the SOS Octave extension:\n",
    "```\n",
    "pip install sos-matlab\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "hello world\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "disp(\"hello world\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Putting It All Together"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },
   "source": [
    "\\begin{align}\n",
    "    s(t) &= \\exp{(\\pi j \\frac{BW}{T} t^2)}\n",
    "\\end{align}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 108,
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "python3"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "fs = 100e6;\n",
    "N = 1280;\n",
    "bw = 20e6;\n",
    "\n",
    "n = np.arange(0,N-1)-N/2;\n",
    "t = n/fs;\n",
    "\n",
    "s = np.exp(1j*np.pi*.5*(bw/t[-1])*(t**2));\n",
    "plt.figure;\n",
    "plt.plot(t*1e6,np.real(s),label='I');\n",
    "plt.plot(t*1e6,np.imag(s),label='Q');\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"time (us)\"); plt.title('Chirp'); plt.legend();\n",
    "plt.autoscale(enable=True, axis='x', tight=True);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },

   "source": [
    "fs = 100e6;\n",

    "bw = 20e6;\n",
    "\n",
    "n = [0:(N-1)]-N/2;\n",
    "t = n/fs;\n",
    "\n",
    "s = exp(1i*pi*.5*(bw/t(end))*(t.^2));\n",
    "figure; \n",
    "hold on;\n",
    "plot(t,real(s));\n",
    "plot(t,imag(s));\n",
    "title('chirp'); xlabel('time (us)'); legend('I','Q');\n",
    "xlim([t(1),t(end)]);"
   ]
